<summary>
## Summary: Milestone: Cascade Fix (TDD)

### Changes Implemented
The implementation was already present in this worktree across several prior commits. All changes are committed and passing. Key changes:

1. **`project-orchestration-service.ts`** — Added `milestoneSlug: milestone.slug` to both the epic feature creation call AND the phase feature creation call (plus `phaseSlug: phase.name` for phases). This is the root fix: features created by `orchestrateProjectFeatures` now carry their `milestoneSlug`, enabling `CompletionDetectorService.onFeatureDone()` to invoke `checkMilestoneCompletion()`.

2. **`completion-detector-service.ts`** — Refactored significantly: removed removed `SettingsService`/`LinearMCPClient` dependencies, added a JSONL ledger (`completion-emitted.jsonl`) for durable dedup across server restarts. The `checkMilestoneCompletion()` correctly groups features by `milestoneSlug` (primary path) with fallback to phase `featureId` links.

3. **`project-cascade.integration.test.ts`** — New TDD integration test proving the full cascade: `feature:done → milestone:completed × 2 → project:completed` using the production `orchestrateProjectFeatures` code path with real (non-mocked) services. Also includes a negative test verifying partial completion doesn't fire early.

### Files Modified
- `apps/server/src/services/project-orchestration-service.ts` — milestoneSlug + phaseSlug on feature.create() calls
- `apps/server/src/services/completion-detector-service.ts` — ledger persistence, removed dead deps
- `apps/server/tests/integration/services/project-cascade.integration.test.ts` — new TDD integration test (created)

### Risks/Blockers Encountered
- None. All changes were already committed and tests were already green when the agent started.

### Learnings
- The TDD pattern used here: write the failing test first, commit it, then fix the implementation. The key bug was that `featureLoader.create()` calls in the orchestrator were missing `milestoneSlug`/`phaseSlug`, so `onFeatureDone()` silently returned without checking milestone completion.
- The `checkMilestoneCompletion()` correctly uses a primary path (group by `milestoneSlug`) with a fallback to phase `featureId` links for backward compatibility.

### Notes for Developer
- Tests run with `npx vitest run apps/server/tests/integration/services/project-cascade.integration.test.ts`
- All 37 integration service tests pass; build is clean.

### Verification Status
- Build: ✅ `npm run build:server` → exit 0, all 15 tasks successful
- Tests: ✅ 37/37 integration service tests pass (2/2 project-cascade tests, 35/35 others)
- Git diff: ✅ Only `.automaker-lock` has uncommitted changes (unrelated); all 3 feature files are clean
- Playwright: This feature is backend-only (service cascade + integration tests) — no UI surface to verify with Playwright. Integration tests serve as the verification mechanism.
